1. **Non-negativity**: Since `a < b`, we have `b - a > 0`. Also, `j + 1 ‚Č• 1` and `n ‚Č• 1` (as `n ‚Č† 0` and `n` is a natural number), so `(j + 1) * (b - a) / n ‚Č• 0`.
2. **Upper Bound**: We need to show that `(j + 1) * (b - a) / n ‚Č§ b - a`, which is equivalent to `(j + 1) / n ‚Č§ 1`. This follows because `j + 1 ‚Č§ n` when `j < n` (since `j ‚ąą range n`).

This ensures the point is in `[a, b]`, and uniform continuity can then be applied.

